.TH "vmware_steal_clock" 9 "vmware_steal_clock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmware_steal_clock \- read the per-cpu steal clock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "uint64_t" vmware_steal_clock
.BI "(int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
the cpu number whose steal clock we want to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function reads the steal clock if we are on a 64-bit system, otherwise
reads it in parts, checking that the high part didn't change in the
meantime.
.SH "RETURN"
The steal clock reading in ns.
